The known ancient cirth do not cover all the sounds of Sindarin: there is no certh for {{angbr|rh}}, {{angbr|lh}}, {{angbr|mh}}, {{angbr|y}} or {{angbr|œ}}. Perhaps this system had been devised for the Old Sindarin tongue, as many of the above-mentioned sounds did not exist in that language.<br/>
However, still frequent sounds {{angbr|w}} and {{angbr|a}} are missing, too. This indicates that some ancient, unknown cirth could have existed, but did not make it to the later systems; a fuller table therefore cannot be reconstructed.<br/>
Long vowels were evidently indicated by doubling.

